\cf0 \'95	Will carry out sustained attacks, sometimes in a "banzai" mode that stops only when there are no armies left anywhere that can attack anything.  In general, though, attacks stop when the player no longer outnumbers its neighboring enemies.\
\'95	Will attempt to eliminate weak players to get their cards.\
\'95	Will choose countries (if playing in that mode), reinforce countries, and attack countries based on a bunch of internal "desirability" metrics.  This includes logic to make the player go after continents, protect their borders, and try to break other players' continents.\
\'95	Will try to move armies that are behind fronts of attack in a direction that makes sense, during the fortify phase.  May hold off an attack if there are nearby friendlies that can be brought in for an extra edge next turn.\
\'95	Will try to sensibly divide armies between a victorious attacking country and a country just conquered, to maximize their effectiveness for continued attacks, or for defense.\
