\cf0 I could go on, but why?  Check the source for what's really happening.  There is still much room for improvement, both in terms of making the player do current activities better, and making it do things it doesn't yet do.  Most of the heuristics in the code follow the 80/20 rule: 20% of the work to accomplish 80% of the benefit.  Still, getting that remaining 20% benefit would make a big difference.\
\
Oh, speaking of the source, it's more or less a shambles, for which I apologize to any unfortunate soul who tries to stumble through it.  Nevertheless, I make it freely available in the public domain to all who are curious.  I ask only that if you create any of your own Risk players, that you send me a copy.  I'm trying to improve my players all the time, and it would be nice to have some fresh blood to pit them against.  :~)\
